EXPO_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_YOUR_KEY_HERE
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_PROJECT.supabase.co
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyYOUR_ANON_KEY_HERE

# ─── RevenueCat (in-app purchases) ───────────────────────────────────────────
# From RevenueCat dashboard → Apps & providers → API keys.
# These are public SDK keys (start with appl_ for iOS, goog_ for Android),
# safe to ship to clients. Different from the webhook secret in Supabase.
# Missing values are tolerated — the SDK simply stays uninitialized and
# purchase flows are unavailable; everything else (Drona chat, tracking) works.
# EXPO_PUBLIC_REVENUECAT_IOS_KEY=appl_YOUR_IOS_KEY_HERE
# EXPO_PUBLIC_REVENUECAT_ANDROID_KEY=goog_YOUR_ANDROID_KEY_HERE

# AI Coach (set in Supabase Edge Function secrets, NOT here)
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-YOUR_KEY_HERE
# CLERK_ISSUER=https://YOUR-CLERK-FRONTEND-API.clerk.accounts.dev
#   ↑ Clerk Dashboard -> API Keys -> "Frontend API URL". Required for both
#   ai-coach and delete-account. The edge functions verify JWTs via this
#   issuer's JWKS endpoint and fail at module load if the var is missing.
# CLERK_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_...   (only delete-account needs this — for the
#   server-side Clerk DELETE /v1/users/{id} call)
# VOYAGE_API_KEY=pa-YOUR_KEY_HERE
#   ↑ https://www.voyageai.com/ -> dashboard. Phase 2.2 onward — the
#   ai-coach edge function uses this to embed user queries at retrieval time.

# ─── Local-only (for the research_kb seed script) ────────────────────────────
# Set both in your shell when running `npx tsx tools/seed-research-kb.ts`:
# VOYAGE_API_KEY=pa-YOUR_KEY_HERE
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=eyYOUR_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY_HERE
#   ↑ Supabase Dashboard -> Settings -> API. Bypasses RLS for the one-off
#   seed. Do NOT put this in EXPO_PUBLIC_* — it must never ship to clients.

# ─── Local-only (for the eval harness: tools/eval/run.ts) ────────────────────
# In addition to VOYAGE_API_KEY and ANTHROPIC_API_KEY:
# SUPABASE_JWT_SECRET=YOUR_HS256_JWT_SECRET
#   ↑ Supabase Dashboard -> Settings -> API -> "JWT Secret". The eval runner
#   signs a synthetic JWT for the `user_eval_alpha` test user so all RLS-bound
#   RPCs respond correctly. Treat like a service-role key — never ship.
# JUDGE_MODEL=claude-opus-4-1-20250805    (optional, defaults to this)

# ─── Required Clerk dashboard config ─────────────────────────────────────────
# Clerk Dashboard -> Authentication -> Add Supabase as a Third-Party Auth
# provider (NOT the legacy "JWT template named supabase" pattern). The
# integration teaches PostgREST + Realtime to trust Clerk's native RS256
# tokens, which our edge functions also verify via JWKS.
